China arrests six after deadly Xinjiang riot - MarketWatch
HONG KONG (MarketWatch) - Chinese police have arrested six suspects after a riot in Kashgar in northwestern Xinjiang province left two policemen and 14 other people dead, local government said on Monday. Police also confiscated explosive devices, homemade guns and knives, according to Tianshan, a news website run by the Xinjiang government. Police were attacked Sunday night as they were detaining suspects in the village of Sayibage in Kona Sheher, a county in Kashgar region, said Tianshan. The police shot and killed 14 people. Two police officers were killed when rioters threw explosives and attacked them with knives, according to the report. A spokeswoman for China's Ministry of Foreign Affairs on Monday described the rioters as "a violent terror gang."

